      "span_text": "AF diagnosis was often corroborated in the patient records, although it was not possible to confirm all AF diagnoses; however, in a sample of 131 patients with AF diagnosed in UK primary care in 2006, 84% were found to have either a primary or secondary care ECG confirmation of their diagnosis.  Care was taken to exclude patients with 'AF resolved'."
